The paper deals with coding problems and sparse matrices, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also introduces a new concept called the hash property, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses maximal-likelihood coding, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG).
